<br>
Kazm is a good magi to start out with because he starts with Giant Baldar.<br>
This is what you want to do on your 1st turn.<br>
1. Play Giant Baldar<br>
2. Draw two cards<br>
Now next turn if they don&#39;t get a stronger creature then Giant Baldar Kazm gets an extra 3e = 8e in total.<br>
2nd turn<br>
1. If he played a bigger creature than Giant Baldar use roar on him and kill the creature.<br>
2. You want to play Baldar to smash the little guys.<br>
<br>
Targ&#39;n should be your next magi. He is very good because of his power enhanced invulnerability. So know your creatures are very strong. By now you should also have a good sized hand so it doesn&#39;t matter that you don&#39;t start out with two of his cards.<br>
1st turn<br>
1. Play hogra stones.<br>
2. Play a strong creature.<br>
There isn&#39;t to much else you can do.<br>
<br>
Hok is last because he will last the longest.<br>
1st turn<br>
1. Play Giant Baldar if you have one.<br>
So know you have only one creature they proably have more than that so they can,t discard him from play with spells, powers, or effects because of Hoks effect.<br>
<br>
Combos <br>
Moga Pup can give 4 energy to another creature so they can survive battle.<br>
<br>
If your magi is weak use Stone Quor squeeze to hurt a strong creature and help your magi.<br>
<br>
Moga can also help win attacks.<br>
<br>
Play Granite Parmalags when Targ&#39;n is out so they loose 3 less energy in attacks.<br>
 <br>
Giant Chougus are good against weave.<br>
<br>
Giant Baldars are good against magi.<br>
<br>
Baldars can kill small creatures.<br>
<br>
Cragnocs can heal and hurt.<br>
<br>
Yark is good for attacking creatures with more then their starting energy. <br>
<br>
Tips:<br>
Relics in this deck have alot to do with luck of the dice so don&#39;t rely on them.<br>
<br>
There arn&#39;t to many spells because this region dosen&#39;t have alot of good ones. The ones in hear are expensive hard hitters.<br>
<br>
Spend your energy wisely. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
